<HTML>

<HEAD>

<TITLE>FACT SHEET -- TRC
</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.0z Beta">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>

<CENTER>
<h2>TRC Fact Sheet</h2>


<b>&quot;We are going to tear apart the whole tax
code...and draft...a dramatic reform.&quot;<br>
<a href="/taxcom/bios.html#Kemp">Jack Kemp</a>, TRC Chairman</b>
</CENTER><hr>


<blockquote>
<P>
<B><a href="/taxcom/dole.html">Origins</a></B>: The 14-member Tax Reform Commission was
appointed by Senate Majority Leader Bob Dole and House Speaker
Newt Gingrich in May, 1995.  The commission held its first public
hearing on June 28, 1995, in Washington, D.C.
<P>
<B><a href="/taxcom/charge.html">Mission</a></B>: Senate Leader Dole and Speaker Gingrich
 have charged the Tax Reform Commission with making recommendations
for a tax code that is &quot;flatter, fairer, and simpler&quot;
- a system that will encourage economic growth and greater opportunity
for all Americans.
<P>
<B><a href="/taxcom/i-pubhr.html">Hearings</a></B>: The Tax Reform Commission held public hearings
from coast-to-coast, in order to reach and hear from a broad cross-section
of Americans.
<br>
 During a three-month period, the commission held
12 public hearings: in Washington, D.C.;   Boston, Massachusetts;
 Omaha, Nebraska;  Charlotte, North Carolina;  Palo Alto, California
(Silicon Valley);  South-central Los Angeles, California;  Harlem
in New York City;  and, Cleveland, Ohio.
<P>
<B>Witnesses</B>: Some 120 witnesses testified before the
commission.  Among those were citizens representing family farms,
inner city business, the high-tech community, academia, small
businesses, large manufacturers, government entities, and Wall
Street.
<P>
<B>Funding</B>: The Tax Reform Commission receives no government
funds.  Expenses are paid by money raised through private contributions.
 Commission members receive no salary or fee for their work performed
on behalf of the TRC.
<P>
<B>Final Report</B>: The commission expects to issue its
final recommendations and report near the beginning of 1996.
<P>
<P>
<center>[ <a href="/taxcom/">TRC Home</a> ]</center>
<P>

</BODY>

