		My question is:  What, in your opinion, are
some of the things we can do to create the proper
groundswell that will give it the necessary momentum
that will cause the lawmakers to make the necessary
leap that we have to make if we all collectively are
going to be successful at replacing the current Tax
Code?<p>

		Yes.  Start with you, Jerry.  And then Frank.<p>

		<b>MR. RENNER:</b>  Well, we could spend a long time
or a short period of time.  I think I'll go short.<p>

		<b>COMMISSIONER CAIN:</b>  Okay.<p>

		<b>MR. RENNER</b>:  It is clear to me that when the
American public is given good information, they almost
always make good decisions.  <p>

		And I wrote a letter to Mr. Gingrich as soon as
