income that farmers have?  How would you attempt to
level that out?  One or two things that you'd like to
see done to do that.<p>

		 <b>MR. HAYES:</b>  Well, it is a difficult question,
because whenever somebody asks me a question about a
particular tax issue, I always say, "It depends on the
circumstances."<p>

		And the reason that I say it, again, goes back
to the way the Code is structured, and that not
everyone fits the same idea or the same solution.<p>

		Not having income-averaging -- that went away
several years ago -- not having any kind of way to
balance your income out, I think it -- your question
really answers itself and that that's why you need a
simplification process.<p>

		I don't know if I can answer that question
specifically and say you need to do this or you need to
do that.  <p>

		But I think what you need to look at is say the
way the system is now.  There's almost nothing you can
do other than, like you said, delay the reporting of
the income until next year; spend as much money this
year as you can, even though you might not really want
to, it might not be the best thing to do.  But I think
simplification goes back to the answer.<p>

		If you know every single year -- when we do tax
planning, we sort of plan two years at a time.  And we
say, "Okay.  Let's look at a two-year span instead of a
one-year span.  And let's try to make as many good
decisions as we can within that two-year span to reduce
your tax burden."<p>

		What I would suggest is that if we go to a
simplified system, then that takes that decision out.  <p>

		I think one of the gentlemen said the amount of
money and effort and time that we spend in this, it
could be spent helping you make other types of
decisions that are going to be beneficial in the long
term, because I really think short-term -- tax
decisions are really short-term decisions.  And as a
businessperson <p>

-- and if you really want to be successful in business,
you have to make long-term decisions. <p>

		So, I think it's more or less tax
simplification is the answer.  I don't have any
specific recommendations that I can give you at this
point.<p>

