by "fairness" in the Tax Code as you envision it?<p>

		<b>MR. HAYES:</b>  Well, my perspective on fairness is
that if a person is doing things to grow their
business, to enhance their wealth, positive efforts
that the tax system be fair to that individual.  <p>

		It wasn't so much relative to one group of
people versus another, or a certain income level versus
another.  It was I need to feel, like, if I'm doing --
if I'm playing the game, if I'm doing it right, if I'm
playing fair as a business person, then the government
is fair with me and not taking away my incentive to do
so.  And I think that's what I meant by "fairness."  <p>

		It wasn't so much relative to different people,
but relative to my own particular situation.<p>

